            <title>[HBASE-2923] Deadlock between HRegion.internalFlushCache and close</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2923</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2461&quot; title=&quot;Split doesn&amp;#39;t handle IOExceptions when creating new region reference files&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-2461&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-2461&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; added a synchronize on close(), but it&apos;s deadlocking with internalFlushCache. We should just check after getting the write locks if the region is already closed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
